16 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Sale of power produced by data center. (1) If electrical power
17 produced by a generator owned by a qualified data center is sold to a public utility or an electric cooperative,
18 the price may not exceed the cost of production.
19 (2) The cost of production includes:
20 (a) the capital cost of constructing the generator;
21 (b) depreciation;
22 (c) wages, salaries, and employee benefits of personnel located at the generator who operate and
23 maintain the facility;
24 (d) fuel;
25 (e) operating supplies and materials;
26 (f) utilities; and
27 (g) contracted services necessary to operate and maintain the generator.
